    <title>Package Manager</title>
    <link href="https://hugaqq.github.io/posts/4777c40b.html"/>
    <id>https://hugaqq.github.io/posts/4777c40b.html</id>
    <published>2026-01-29T06:10:00.000Z</published>
    <updated>2026-01-29T22:07:23.456Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h1 id="Package-Manager"><a href="#Package-Manager" class="headerlink" title="Package Manager"></a>Package Manager</h1><h1 id="Python"><a href="#Python" class="headerlink" title="Python"></a>Python</h1><ul><li>Key : Create a relatively independent environment in project folder to avoid influencing the whole environment.</li><li>In MacOS, because of <strong><code>Homebrew</code></strong> (another package manager) locked the python environment to avoid conflicts between different PMs. So we should use some tools to create virtual environments independently.</li></ul><h2 id="venv"><a href="#venv" class="headerlink" title="venv"></a><code>venv</code></h2><ul><li>In Python, in-built function <code>venv</code> is useful.</li></ul><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">python venv .venv <span class="comment"># python venv [your_config_folder]</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># Create a virtual environment</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line"><span class="built_in">source</span> .venv/bin/activate <span class="comment"># activate the virtual environment</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">(venv) deactivate. <span class="comment"># deactivate the virtual environment</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><ul><li>Principle</li></ul><p>Let’s explain what happened in upper orders</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br><span class="line">11</span><br><span class="line">12</span><br><span class="line">13</span><br><span class="line">14</span><br><span class="line">15</span><br><span class="line">16</span><br><span class="line">17</span><br><span class="line">18</span><br><span class="line">19</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">1. python venv .venv</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># the structure of `.venv`</span></span><br><span class="line">.venv/</span><br><span class="line">├── bin/ (Windows 下叫 Scripts/)</span><br><span class="line">│   ├── python        <span class="comment"># 指向系统 Python 的快捷方式</span></span><br><span class="line">│   ├── python3       <span class="comment"># 同上</span></span><br><span class="line">│   ├── pip           <span class="comment"># 该环境专用的包管理脚本</span></span><br><span class="line">│   └── activate      <span class="comment"># 一个用来修改 PATH 的 Shell 脚本</span></span><br><span class="line">├── include/          <span class="comment"># 编译某些 C 语言扩展包时需要的头文件</span></span><br><span class="line">├── lib/</span><br><span class="line">│   └── python3.x/</span><br><span class="line">│       └── site-packages/ <span class="comment"># 你所有 pip install 的包都躺在这里</span></span><br><span class="line">└── pyvenv.cfg        <span class="comment"># 【最关键的配置文件】</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">2. <span class="built_in">source</span> .venv/bin/activate</span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># change $PATH, moving &#x27;.venv/bin/&#x27; to the frontest</span></span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># to let the sys search bags first in .venv/lib/python3.x</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">3. deactivate <span class="comment"># the shell script details</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><hr><h2 id="pipx"><a href="#pipx" class="headerlink" title="pipx"></a><code>pipx</code></h2><ul><li>What : pipx will create a virtual environment for every tool</li><li>How : the usage of <code>pipx</code></li></ul><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">pipx install &lt;package&gt; <span class="comment">#install</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">pipx run &lt;package&gt; <span class="comment">#temporary run (download automatically)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">pipx list <span class="comment">#list all packages downloaded by pipx</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">pipx upgrade &lt;package&gt;</span><br><span class="line">pipx upgrade-all <span class="comment">#upgrade</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">pip uninstall <span class="comment">#remove </span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><ul><li><p>Principle : just like <code>venv</code></p><p>  it will create <code>venvs</code> in <code>~/.local/share/pipx/venvs/</code>, and put all packages in this folder</p></li></ul><h2 id="pipx-venv"><a href="#pipx-venv" class="headerlink" title="pipx &amp; venv"></a><code>pipx</code> &amp; <code>venv</code></h2><ul><li>venv ‘s priority is higher than pipx.</li></ul><h2 id="UV"><a href="#UV" class="headerlink" title="UV"></a>UV</h2><ul><li>a powerful package manager that replace <code>pip</code> <code>venv</code> <code>pyenv</code> <code>poetry</code></li><li>how to use <code>uv</code></li></ul><p><code>uv python</code> git of python</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">uv python list </span><br><span class="line"><span class="comment"># list all avilable versions of python ( online and downloaded)</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">uv python install &lt;version_num&gt;</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><code>uv venv</code> </p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">uv venv <span class="comment"># create a folder that contains .venv</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">uv venv -- python &lt;version&gt; <span class="comment"># in specific version</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><code>uv pip</code> package manage</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">uv pip install &lt;package&gt;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">uv pip list</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">uv pip install -r requirements.txt <span class="comment"># install the old requirements</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p><code>uv</code> for project</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">uv init &lt;folder&gt; <span class="comment"># (create) and init a folder to a industrial project folder</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">uv add &lt;package&gt; <span class="comment"># download</span></span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">uv <span class="built_in">sync</span> <span class="comment"># recover the original settings</span></span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><h1 id="Other"><a href="#Other" class="headerlink" title="Other"></a>Other</h1><ul><li><code>homebrew</code></li><li><code>npm</code>, <code>pnpm</code></li></ul>]]></content>
    
    
      
      
